    "title": "Synergy",
    "description": "&quot;Something hit me very hard once, thinking about what one little man could do.&quot;\n\n&quot;The highest of generalizations is the synergetic integration of truth and love.&quot;\n\n&quot;There is a synergetic progression in Universe—a hierarchy of total complex behaviors entirely unpredicted by their successive subcomplexes' behaviors. It is manifest that Universe is the maximum synergy-of-synergies, being utterly unpredicted by any of its parts. &quot;\n\n&quot;Dear reader, traditional human power structures and their reign of darkness are about to be rendered obsolete.&quot;\n\n-R. Bucky Fuller\n\n&quot;How wonderful is Death,\nDeath and his brother Sleep!&quot;\n\n-Percy Bysshe Shelley, Queen Mab",
